<section class="py-16 bg-base-100 sm:py-20">
  <div class="px-4 mx-auto max-w-4xl sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold sm:text-4xl xl:text-5xl">
        Common questions.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto">
      <p>
        <strong>How long have you been dealing with clusters?</strong><br>
        Over a decade. Built this in 2024 when I was desperate. I know the 2am
        scrambles, the oxygen fights, the "just drink water" advice. Every
        feature comes from personal pain.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Will this help me get oxygen approved?</strong><br>
        Multiple users said our reports finally convinced their insurance. Clean
        data beats "I have bad headaches" every time. No promises, but it's
        worked for others.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Is it really free? What's the catch?</strong><br>
        Zero catch. I pay for servers myself. There's a donate button if you
        want, but no pressure. This isn't a startup. It's a tool I needed, now
        we all have it.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Can I track during an attack when I can barely see?</strong><br>
        YES. Massive button. One tap. Done. Add details later when you're human.
        I designed this mid-cycle, so I know what's possible when you can't think.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>What about my privacy?</strong><br>
        No email needed. No ads. No tracking. German servers with strict privacy
        laws. Your pain data stays yours. I wouldn't want mine sold, so yours
        won't be.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-12">
      <%= link_to faq_path, class: "btn btn-lg btn-outline" do %>
        See All Questions
        <%= heroicon "arrow-right", variant: "mini", class: "w-5 h-5" %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
